stylometry: THe total cost of managing a product in inventory equals a fixed cost plus a variable cost.  The costs you are balancing include holding costs and ordering costs.  Each company is different but you can calculate the total cost by understanding what each company uses for variable costs.  SOme companies are charged a certain price per product for holding and ordering costs.  Other companies only charge one fixed cost for ordering or holding a product.  A company has to decide to balance these two costs and decided which one makes the most sense for their situation.  If it costs .25 cents to hold order each product and you order 1 million products thats alot more money wise then lets say a fixed cost of 5,000 dollars for the whole year.  Now this is an extreme example of a problem but stills shows the same conclusion.  You need to be able to balance the fixed and variable costs based on the ordering and holding costs.
